.TH OPENTELEMETRY-NODEJS 1 "@DATE@" "opentelemetry-nodejs-autoinstrumentation @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
opentelemetry-nodejs \- OpenTelemetry Node.js Auto-Instrumentation
.SH SYNOPSIS
The Node.js agent is loaded automatically by the OpenTelemetry Injector when a
Node.js application starts. Manual usage:
.PP
.B node --require /usr/lib/opentelemetry/nodejs/node_modules/@opentelemetry/auto-instrumentations-node/build/src/register.js
.I app.js
.SH DESCRIPTION
The OpenTelemetry Node.js Auto-Instrumentation package automatically instruments
Node.js applications to collect distributed traces, metrics, and logs without
requiring code changes.
.PP
When used with the OpenTelemetry Injector package, the agent is automatically
loaded into all Node.js processes.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B /usr/lib/opentelemetry/nodejs/
Directory containing the Node.js instrumentation packages.
.TP
.B /etc/opentelemetry/nodejs/otel-config.yaml
Optional declarative configuration file.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B OTEL_SERVICE_NAME
Set the service name for telemetry data.
.TP
.B OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT
Set the OTLP exporter endpoint (e.g., http://localhost:4317).
.TP
.B OTEL_TRACES_EXPORTER
Set the traces exporter (otlp, console, none). Default: otlp
.TP
.B OTEL_METRICS_EXPORTER
Set the metrics exporter (otlp, console, none). Default: otlp
.TP
.B OTEL_LOGS_EXPORTER
Set the logs exporter (otlp, console, none). Default: otlp
.TP
.B OTEL_SDK_DISABLED
Set to "true" to disable the SDK. Default: false
.TP
.B OTEL_EXPERIMENTAL_CONFIG_FILE
Path to a declarative configuration file.
.SH EXAMPLES
Manually run a Node.js application with instrumentation:
.PP
.RS
OTEL_SERVICE_NAME=myapp node \\
  --require /usr/lib/opentelemetry/nodejs/node_modules/@opentelemetry/auto-instrumentations-node/build/src/register.js \\
  app.js
.RE
